Army Wives - Season 7, Episode 14 (Series Finale Special)




A Final Salute

After seven tours of duty, Lifetime celebrates the legacy of its longest-running series with this two-hour special. The retrospective provides a look back at the program with members of the cast and production team as they come together for a final heartfelt goodbye to "Army Wives." Features interviews with original cast members, including Kim Delaney, Sally Pressman, Brigid Brannagh, Wendy Davis, Sterling K. Brown, Brian McNamara, Terry Serpico, Drew Fuller and Jeremy Davidson, who reunite to offer exclusive insight in to the show and their characters. Executive producer Jeff Melvoin and author Tanya Biank, whose book the drama is based upon, also join in to reminisce about their experience on "Army Wives." The special also features commentary from real-life military wives.




Original Air Date: 16-Mar-2014
